Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.82,0:00:07.66,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Now Silver Sword's here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.66,0:00:08.99,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Look, another one!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.99,0:00:10.16,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.16,0:00:14.49,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,There are many guilds, with many different goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.86,0:00:19.79,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,There are combat guilds, \Nwhose primary goal is to get stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.55,0:00:22.79,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,In Akihabara, the major ones are
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.69,0:00:25.28,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}D.D.D. \NPlayer Count \N{\fs20}1,534 Players
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.72,0:00:24.67,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,D.D.D.,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.92,0:00:27.78,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Black Sword Knights \N{\fs20}Player Count \N186 Players
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.14,0:00:27.23,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,the Black Sword Knights,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.98,0:00:30.29,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9}Honesty \N{\fs20}Player Count \N743 Players
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.63,0:00:29.58,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Honesty,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.50,0:00:32.79,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}West Wind Brigade \N{\fs20}Player Count \N64 Players
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.05,0:00:32.31,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,the West Wind Brigade,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.05,0:00:37.29,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9}Silver Sword \N{\fs20}Player Count \N220 Players
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.26,0:00:36.39,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Silver Sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.85,0:00:40.31,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,There are also crafting guilds,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.31,0:00:44.24,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,whose time is primarily occupied by \Namassing items or selling them in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.54,0:00:47.80,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9}Marine Agency \N{\fs20}Player Count \N2,547 Players
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.37,0:00:47.42,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Marine Agency,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.00,0:00:50.31,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9}Roderic Merchant Guild \N{\fs20}Player Count \N1,881 Players
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.72,0:00:49.89,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Roderic Merchant Guild,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.50,0:00:52.81,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Shopping Street 8 \N{\fs20}Player Count \N669 Players
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.20,0:00:52.45,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Shopping Street 8,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.01,0:00:54.81,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9}Grandeur \N{\fs20}Player Count \N31 Players
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.77,0:00:54.82,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Grandeur,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.07,0:00:56.81,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Radio Market \N{\fs20}Player Count \N21 Players
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.75,0:00:56.82,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Radio Market.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.07,0:01:02.32,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Crescent Moon Alliance \N{\fs20}Player Count \N24 Players
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.87,0:01:01.10,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And there's the support guild, \NMarielle's Crescent Moon Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.53,0:01:02.33,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.69,0:01:06.75,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Log Horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.46,0:01:08.49,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9}Log Horizon \N{\fs20}Player Count \N4 Players
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.62,0:01:11.82,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,So all the major guilds' masters are here?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.14,0:01:14.53,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.11,0:03:01.03,Title,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1606,1)}Round Table Conference
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.84,0:02:58.27,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Round Table Conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.56,0:03:05.01,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's a good sign that everyone came.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.97,0:03:08.83,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Asking Soujirou to handle the \Ninvitations was the right move.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.74,0:03:17.88,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you all for taking the time to come today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.49,0:03:23.26,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I am Shiroe, of the guild Log Horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.73,0:03:26.66,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,You can keep the introductions short,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.66,0:03:28.73,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe of the Tea Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.93,0:03:29.31,HUD1,I,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Isaac \N{\fs20}Race/ Human \NGuardian, Lv. 90 \NBlack Sword Knights
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.92,0:03:31.75,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Isaac.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.12,0:03:34.31,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised and honored \Nthat you remember me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.76,0:03:36.24,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,How could I forget?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.49,0:03:38.32,Default,W,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.61,0:03:41.86,HUD1,I,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9}William Massachusetts {\fs20}\NRace/ Elf \NAssassin, Lv. 90 \NSilver Sword
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.89,0:03:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are we here, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.87,0:03:48.41,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I've brought you here for input and aid, \Nconcerning Akihabara's present state.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.53,0:03:51.83,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,As you know, ever since the Apocalypse,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.47,0:03:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we've been trapped in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.34,0:03:58.84,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And there's no way to know if \Nwe'll be able to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.63,0:04:02.57,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Given the circumstances, I'd like to \Nkeep the situation in Akihabara
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.57,0:04:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from getting any worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.17,0:04:06.91,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,That's a lot to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.30,0:04:09.47,Default,Guild,0000,0000,0000,,Are you thinking of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.06,0:04:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,something similar to the failed attempt \Nto form alliances of the smaller guilds?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.64,0:04:14.27,HUD1,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9}Crusty \N{\fs20}Race/ Human \NGuardian, Lv. 90 \ND.D.D
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.94,0:04:15.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Similar, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.34,0:04:17.15,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.89,0:04:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard that that plan was halted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.78,0:04:24.48,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Ichimonjinosuke Akaneya \N{\fs20}Race/ Human \NSorcerer, Lv. 90 \NRadio Market
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.87,0:04:24.49,Default,Ak,0000,0000,0000,,That plan had many problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.43,0:04:30.58,Default,Ak,0000,0000,0000,,It was the smaller guilds' attempt to unite, \Nto compete with the larger ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.79,0:04:37.46,HUD1,Ak,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Woodstock W. \N{\fs20}Race/ Dwarf \NAssassin, Lv. 90 \NGrandeur
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.30,0:04:34.80,Default,Wo,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, they wanted \Nto protect their interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.80,0:04:37.18,Default,Wo,0000,0000,0000,,They were only concerned with themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.65,0:04:43.91,HUD1,Wo,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9}Eins \N{\fs20}Race/ Human \NShrine Priest, Lv. 90 \NHonesty
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.00,0:04:41.31,Default,Ei,0000,0000,0000,,Then is your goal today to gather \Nthe major powers in Akihabara,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.31,0:04:43.91,Default,Ei,0000,0000,0000,,to prevent the collision of interests?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.32,0:04:47.97,Default,Wi,0000,0000,0000,,That won't happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.22,0:04:50.02,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone seems to assume
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.02,0:04:54.09,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,that this would be a continuation \Nof the first failed alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.09,0:04:57.98,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Correcting them quickly would be best.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.65,0:05:00.32,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That is not the intent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.85,0:05:04.99,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,My only goal here is to improve \Nthe situation in Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.47,0:05:07.91,Default,Wi,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll be on my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.53,0:05:10.69,Default,Wi,0000,0000,0000,,We are a combat guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.23,0:05:13.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have no interest in the city itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.69,0:05:17.51,Default,Wi,0000,0000,0000,,That's merely where we go to sell our items.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.51,0:05:18.25,Default,Wi,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.71,0:05:22.25,Default,Wi,0000,0000,0000,,the city's condition doesn't matter to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.45,0:05:29.43,Default,Wi,0000,0000,0000,,Let those who care about the \Ncity solve its problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.28,0:05:33.17,Default,Wi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe there's anything \Nwrong with discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.11,0:05:36.45,Default,Wi,0000,0000,0000,,But I do think it's a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.16,0:05:41.15,Default,Wi,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless, we aren't interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.38,0:05:43.15,Default,Wi,0000,0000,0000,,Do it without us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.26,0:05:47.21,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Silver Sword's out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.21,0:05:49.27,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,An expected scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.85,0:05:51.16,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.60,0:05:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's such an important day,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.62,0:05:57.72,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,but I haven't seen Akatsuki or Naotsugu...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.72,0:06:00.56,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Or even Shouryuu and Hien all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.56,0:06:02.23,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.23,0:06:04.42,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they're busy with something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.10,0:06:08.09,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.09,0:06:09.96,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,That we can escape from here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.96,0:06:12.35,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I got word this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.20,0:06:17.66,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as Tohya and the rest depart to \Nhunt, leave the guild hall with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.62,0:06:20.01,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,Take all the new players with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.60,0:06:22.60,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,You need only walk out the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.44,0:06:27.40,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,A female assassin named Akatsuki \Nwill be in the Guild Building.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.17,0:06:31.80,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,And just in case, a guardian named \NNaotsugu will be in the Cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.40,0:06:36.37,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,I can't be with you, but don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.60,0:06:40.00,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,The entire Guild Building is under my control.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.59,0:06:45.25,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,He said we only need to go out the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.74,0:06:47.31,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,Just run straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.31,0:06:48.57,Default - flashback,All,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.11,0:06:52.73,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,But what does he mean that the \NGuild Building is under his control?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.73,0:06:55.92,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know, but all we have \Nto do is run out the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.23,0:06:57.01,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.15,0:06:59.96,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What are you whispering about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.96,0:07:01.57,Default,M/Girl,0000,0000,0000,,N-Nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.96,0:07:01.57,Default,M/Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Not a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.21,0:07:04.37,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'll continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.35,0:07:07.25,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I've gathered you here
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.25,0:07:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to help create a council to \Ndiscuss Akihabara's problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.22,0:07:13.57,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,A Round Table conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.04,0:07:19.65,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Our immediate goal will be to improve \Nthe city's atmosphere and safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.57,0:07:21.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,In the long term,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.78,0:07:25.76,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like us to be capable of addressing \Ndifferent types of problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.98,0:07:28.96,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,This is where it gets serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.91,0:07:31.05,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Before we get to that,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.01,0:07:35.74,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,can you tell us how you chose \Nthose you invited today?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.08,0:07:37.08,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.53,0:07:41.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,First, the Black Sword Knights, Honesty,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.98,0:07:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D.D.D., and the West Wind Brigade
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.37,0:07:50.90,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,were chosen as the largest or most \Nnotable of the combat guilds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.52,0:07:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Same for Silver Sword, \Nwhich is no longer with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.19,0:07:56.82,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Marine Agency, Roderic Merchant Guild,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.82,0:08:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Shopping Street 8 were chosen \Nto represent the crafting guilds.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.06,0:08:04.24,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The Crescent Moon Alliance, \NGrandeur, and Radio Market
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.60,0:08:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,represent not only their own guilds,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.06,0:08:12.76,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,but the smaller guilds, as well as \Nplayers who don't belong to one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.30,0:08:14.51,Default,Wi,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.91,0:08:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Around 6,000 players in the guilds \Nare represented here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.99,0:08:24.14,Default,Ak,0000,0000,0000,,Which means 9,000 players in the city either
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.14,0:08:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,don't belong to one or are in a smaller one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.97,0:08:29.05,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,And you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.05,0:08:32.51,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I am here as meeting organizer and the \None who came up with the proposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.19,0:08:36.51,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Log Horizon only has four members.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.51,0:08:40.54,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, they wouldn't have the right \Nto participate in this conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.83,0:08:42.00,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.96,0:08:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you put this meeting together and invited us,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.76,0:08:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that you would have the right to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.68,0:08:50.80,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.09,0:08:56.18,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we form this council you're talking \Nabout, how will we keep the peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.71,0:09:01.66,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,No, what do you mean, exactly, \Nby the city being unsafe?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.19,0:09:04.75,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You're all aware
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.75,0:09:09.32,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,that certain guilds are locking up new players \Nunder the guise of protection, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.89,0:09:16.36,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,You're talking about the EXP pots.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.44,0:09:19.70,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Listen up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.90,0:09:21.36,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's time to go hunting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.74,0:09:24.26,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Get ready and meet, up front.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.63,0:09:27.52,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Crafters, be sure to reach your quotas.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.52,0:09:28.78,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.35,0:09:32.71,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.12,0:09:35.22,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,we're ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.20,0:09:38.34,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,One cough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.78,0:09:39.72,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.90,0:09:42.04,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, time to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.38,0:09:47.42,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,But that isn't illegal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.18,0:09:50.06,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Currently, in this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.43,0:09:52.19,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,there are no laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.19,0:09:53.58,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, there are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.58,0:09:56.39,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,There are No Combat zones.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.95,0:10:00.39,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's simply a defensive system attacking players
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.39,0:10:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who fight in No Combat areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.59,0:10:08.57,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't a law, but a natural phenomenon, \Nlike any other.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.23,0:10:10.20,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.79,0:10:14.61,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Laws are what people create, \Nand others recognize.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.61,0:10:16.75,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,That's what Henrietta said.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.00,0:10:20.76,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,A few days ago, I went to Susukino.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.20,0:10:22.51,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Susukino?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.43,0:10:25.72,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,A guild there was trying
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.09,0:10:31.36,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,to control the city, and threatening \NNPCs and other players.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.22,0:10:35.87,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,By your previous logic, that is not illegal,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.87,0:10:37.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,since the system doesn't attack them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.55,0:10:41.28,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But is that really all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.80,0:10:43.61,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all that the law is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.63,0:10:48.56,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe is trying to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.56,0:10:52.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that we need laws to bind us, \Nin this lawless world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.04,0:10:55.75,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone seems to be wavering.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.18,0:10:59.30,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Some think rules of some form are necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.07,0:11:03.35,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Some think we'll never be able \Nto reach such an agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.12,0:11:10.01,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,But what will you do if a group appears that \Nrefuses to recognize this Round Table?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.54,0:11:12.86,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,A group that goes against anything we decide?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.11,0:11:14.23,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We will fight them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.65,0:11:15.59,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Fight them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.30,0:11:17.44,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.86,0:11:19.76,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Banish them from Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.54,0:11:23.05,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And if necessary, of course, \Nwe'd force them to disband.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.42,0:11:24.94,Default,Ak,0000,0000,0000,,Banish...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.94,0:11:29.90,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,But you can't kill anyone in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.63,0:11:37.21,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, you won't be able to do \Nit without combat guilds, like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.84,0:11:42.57,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,If the major guilds here say they \Ndon't care about the conference,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.57,0:11:45.72,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,or about your laws...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.36,0:11:48.29,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's war.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.05,0:11:54.23,Default,Ei,0000,0000,0000,,If the major guilds were to go out of control, \Nthere'd be no way to stop them...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.46,0:11:59.23,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I must say that this doesn't strike me as realistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.89,0:12:03.11,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I believe forming this Round Table is worthwhile.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.02,0:12:09.81,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,But it would be mostly for show, without any real—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.93,0:12:20.41,Default,{S,0000,0000,0000,,Today, approximately four hours ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.27,0:12:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I purchased the Guild Building's zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.16,0:12:32.22,HUD1,{S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Guild Building {\fs18}\NJapan Server \NAkihabara \NCity/ No Monsters \NNo PVP \NEntry Restrictions/ None \NExit Restrictions/ None
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.23,0:12:33.77,HUD1,{S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\fs18}Owner \N{\fs22}Shiroe \N{\fs18}Guild \N{\fs22}Log Horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.57,0:12:36.19,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What did you just say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.28,0:12:38.65,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Impressive...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.09,0:12:42.32,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, I have the authority \Nto control the zone's settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.08,0:12:46.57,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Including who enters and leaves the zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.58,0:12:51.33,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, anyone I put on the blacklist
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.13,0:12:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,won't be able to access the Guild Building at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.01,0:12:59.59,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.83,0:13:01.99,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,He's a real villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.24,0:13:03.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.09,0:13:14.25,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,What does his buying the Guild Building mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.81,0:13:20.48,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,The Guild Building's zone is now \NShiroe's private property.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.13,0:13:24.10,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Why would that be a problem for people?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.10,0:13:29.37,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone Shiroe doesn't want entering \Nthe Guild Building, won't be able to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.74,0:13:34.87,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,But the large guilds have their guild halls elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.29,0:13:40.88,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,To create, join, or leave a guild, \Nyou have to come to the Guild Building.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.15,0:13:45.63,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,And the bank is here, also.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.99,0:13:49.44,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Walking around with lots of money is dangerous,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.44,0:13:56.02,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,so most players keep the majority \Nof their assets here...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.52,0:13:58.65,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Including valuable belongings.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.30,0:14:04.98,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Since a bank is located in every town, \Nyou can make a withdrawal anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.83,0:14:08.85,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,But with the Transport Gates off-line,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.85,0:14:12.11,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,travel to other cities is almost impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.11,0:14:13.16,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.16,0:14:21.84,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe can prevent any Akihabara adventurer \Nfrom accessing their own bank account.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.84,0:14:25.67,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Then that makes him just like a bad guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.98,0:14:32.22,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe makes the devil himself \Nlook meek and mild.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.77,0:14:38.21,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The devil knows he's a bad boy, \Nbut Shiroe doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.82,0:14:42.71,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The nickname "Villain in Glasses" is too generous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.23,0:14:48.20,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,A zone's owner has the right to control \Nwho enters and leaves it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.20,0:14:51.72,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But they can also designate areas \Nto allow or prohibit combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.55,0:14:58.12,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Given their need to control the new players,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.12,0:15:00.40,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Hamelin's guild hall should allow combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.09,0:15:03.39,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Quick, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.15,0:15:10.29,Default,Ninja,0000,0000,0000,,I thought something was suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.67,0:15:12.39,Default,Ninja,0000,0000,0000,,Where are the other kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.21,0:15:15.00,Default,Ninja,0000,0000,0000,,What are you planning?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.32,0:15:18.58,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,Remember what Shiroe taught you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.50,0:15:24.43,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.56,0:15:28.88,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,The samurai skills Shrike Impalement \Nand Lanius Capture...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.31,0:15:32.99,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,These temporarily mute an enemy, \Nstopping it from casting spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.66,0:15:33.57,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Go on ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.57,0:15:34.43,Default,Girls,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.85,0:15:42.62,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,Lanius Capture lasts fifteen seconds!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.15,0:15:45.88,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's about to run out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.53,0:15:49.63,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,The shrine priest's healing ability, \NDamage Interception...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.04,0:15:54.14,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,It sets a barrier that absorbs damage \Nup to a certain amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.41,0:15:55.89,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Shiroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.55,0:15:58.03,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You bastards...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.34,0:16:03.55,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'll send you to the Cathedral a hundred times!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.97,0:16:05.30,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Stop yelling...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.30,0:16:06.44,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.83,0:16:09.61,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The kids ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.63,0:16:15.87,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.16,0:16:17.14,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.34,0:16:20.87,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord, the escape has begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.76,0:16:24.79,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What's he laughing about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.06,0:16:27.37,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,But keeping us from our banks...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.37,0:16:29.49,Default,Ak,0000,0000,0000,,That's blackmail.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.49,0:16:31.53,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I simply answered his question.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.09,0:16:34.46,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who opposes the Round Table
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.92,0:16:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will lose access rights to the Guild Banks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.11,0:16:40.06,Default,Ak,0000,0000,0000,,That's why it's blackmail.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.06,0:16:45.71,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Then, "If we have to, we'll start \Na war," is also blackmail, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.23,0:16:52.80,Default,Ai,0000,0000,0000,,Purchasing the Guild Building's zone should \Nrequire an astronomical amount of funds.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.18,0:16:55.32,Default,Ak,0000,0000,0000,,Where'd you get the money?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.99,0:16:57.59,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Five million.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.43,0:17:00.19,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We gave him the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.06,0:17:06.04,Default,Ro,0000,0000,0000,,Then the quest you were leading...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.62,0:17:08.17,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't a quest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.62,0:17:10.84,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It was to create this council.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.13,0:17:13.01,Default,Ak,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.20,0:17:17.45,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.45,0:17:18.68,Default - flashback,Ro,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.46,0:17:23.24,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,Something this simple was \NCrescent Moon's recipe?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.24,0:17:26.69,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You made us pay for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.45,0:17:31.40,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think this isn't worth
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.21,0:17:33.78,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,five million?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.40,0:17:42.08,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We're almost there, Minori!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.01,0:17:50.25,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't your lucky day, kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.04,0:17:50.24,HUD1,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Schreider \N{\fs20}Race/ Human \NSummoner, Lv. 46 \NHamelin
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.53,0:17:52.75,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.04,0:17:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.78,0:17:56.25,SignB,T,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}In Combat \N{\3c&H12080B&}Tohya \N{\fs20}Race/ Human \NSamurai, Lv. 15 \NAccuracy Down \NSustained Damage \NHamelin \N\N\NZone Information \N{\c&HD0D3F4&\3c&H151569&}All skills permitted.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.13,0:17:55.94,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! At this rate...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.60,0:17:58.10,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,Pentagram Barrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.88,0:18:02.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.20,0:18:05.27,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,My level is higher...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.27,0:18:06.51,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's higher!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.51,0:18:08.79,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad, kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.44,0:18:10.70,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.43,0:18:12.87,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Minori!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.13,0:18:15.32,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Schreider?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.32,0:18:17.83,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You're late. Drag the kids back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.83,0:18:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.93,0:18:22.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Minori!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.12,0:18:23.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.73,0:18:48.32,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya, it's not safe here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.32,0:18:49.60,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.16,0:18:52.67,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.67,0:18:54.23,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The door...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.61,0:18:58.73,HUD1,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\fs18}Zone Setting:                                                                            Guild Building\NAccess Restricted                                                                      Owner: Shiroe\NGuild: Log Horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.61,0:18:58.73,HUD1,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\an6\fs18}ID Recognition                                                                   Zone Information:\NSmoking Thunder   Guild/ Hamelin                              No Combat Allowed\NAccess: Not Allowed                                                                     No Skill Use
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.39,0:18:57.10,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,A character who owns a zone
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.10,0:18:58.74,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,can control who enters and exits.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.37,0:19:02.28,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,They can add someone to a list, \Nand prevent their entering.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.95,0:19:04.05,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.05,0:19:05.74,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,No one's following us...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.13,0:19:07.69,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,So you're the last two?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.68,0:19:09.89,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Shouryuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.35,0:19:12.25,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe sent me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.68,0:19:13.77,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,He did?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.27,0:19:16.13,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Where is everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.13,0:19:17.51,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Waiting at the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.18,0:19:21.03,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.03,0:19:22.89,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, you can deal with—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.13,0:19:25.14,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, let's get to the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.14,0:19:25.93,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.93,0:19:27.59,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,I told you— Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.59,0:19:29.05,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,You stupid fox!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.05,0:19:32.03,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,That'll cause trouble for Mari— \NI mean, the guild master!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.20,0:19:32.03,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.45,0:19:36.36,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, quit stumbling around. You look pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.99,0:19:39.66,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You're so mean, Tohya.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.10,0:19:49.43,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It hurts, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.43,0:19:53.08,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,But this doesn't count as combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.65,0:19:56.84,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do to the guild hall?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.63,0:19:58.96,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What's that look for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.10,0:20:01.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.14,0:20:03.10,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get cocky, brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.10,0:20:04.81,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,There's nowhere you can go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.38,0:20:09.56,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Both of us... We have nowhere to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.54,0:20:16.22,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.22,0:20:20.61,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I was sure I'd added every member \Nof Hamelin to the blacklist.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.06,0:20:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.40,0:20:23.84,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? My lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.50,0:20:26.37,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, I missed one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.76,0:20:28.12,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,His name is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.18,0:20:30.66,SignD,,0000,0000,0000,,Schreider/ Adventurer
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.80,0:20:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Schreider?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.85,0:20:31.98,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Just as the name suggests,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.98,0:20:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,his face looks like it's been through a shredder.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.46,0:20:36.29,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.29,0:20:39.20,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you babbling about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.34,0:20:42.40,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What just...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.07,0:20:45.68,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Ow! Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.68,0:20:49.14,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,So this doesn't count as combat, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.63,0:20:53.26,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really glad to hear that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.27,0:20:57.22,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,M-My luck's run out...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.65,0:21:00.35,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,One down, shrimp.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.35,0:21:01.88,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Don't call me "shrimp"!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.32,0:21:05.01,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya and Minori, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.54,0:21:06.94,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Akatsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.94,0:21:09.16,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a ninja of my lord, Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.66,0:21:12.30,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You and your friends are safe now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.69,0:21:16.11,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord is fighting on another battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.18,0:21:21.36,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we start by getting you a bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.97,0:21:27.18,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You still have other things \Nto say, don't you, Shiroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.82,0:21:29.41,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.41,0:21:31.60,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.60,0:21:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you're still in a position to blackmail us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.99,0:21:37.83,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Do you all really think that this town...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.83,0:21:43.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, all this world's adventurers \Nare okay as things currently are?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.46,0:21:46.81,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I have two goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.67,0:21:50.72,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,First, to restore life to everyone in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.72,0:21:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And in the long term, in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.28,0:21:56.25,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,My other is
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.99,0:22:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to create laws that, if nothing else, \Nbind the people of this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.46,0:22:05.76,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Does anyone here oppose these two goals?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.39,0:22:12.67,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord, the escape was a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.40,0:22:16.95,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I told you to stop laughing!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.29,0:22:24.03,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,If you're that insistent, then I'll \Nmake a proposal of my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.81,0:22:29.83,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you tell us specifically \Nwhat Log Horizon has in mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.44,0:24:10.20,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe succeeds in rescuing the new \Nplayers, but his battle continues.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.20,0:24:13.75,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,His goal is to create a place where he belongs.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.75,0:24:16.10,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,But it belongs to more than himself alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.60,0:24:18.91,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,He has friends and those needing his protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.28,0:24:23.25,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,A place where they can sit under \Nthe stars, eating curry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.56,0:24:30.99,Title,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Grab It in Your Hand
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.81,0:24:25.89,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Grab It in Your Hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.34,0:24:27.80,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,This is our reality.
